newsitem.title: USA: U.S. Midcontinent unleaded, diesel prices steady.
newsitem.headline: U.S. Midcontinent unleaded, diesel prices steady.

text.p: U.S. Midcontinent unleaded gasoline and diesel fuel prices were largely unchanged late Wednesday after surging earlier in the day on firming futures prices, traders said.
Products differentials in Chicago and Group Three were steady in the wake of rising NYMEX front-month unleaded gasoline and heating oil prices on the day, traders said.
Traders said plentiful diesel inventories in the region should eventually pull low sulphur diesel basis lower, but not before the futures prices moderate on the NYMEX.
"I expect we'll move closer to two cents over (the print) in the Group eventually," one trader said.
Group Three low sulphur diesel remained 4.0/4.25 cents over the print for prompt deliveries and eased to 3.00/3.25 cents over for later deliveries late Wednesday.
Chicago low sulphur diesel eased to 1.25/1.50 cents over the print for prompt and later deliveries.
High sulphur was talked 2.0 cents over the print for prompt deliveries and a cent weaker for later deliveries in Group Three, and 0.25/0.50 cent over the print in Chicago.
Unleaded remained 1.0/1.25 cent over the print for prompt deliveries and 0.25 cent under to even with the print for later deliveries in both Chicago and Group Three.
